Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells function as promising power generation devices in the 21 century, but the lack of effective active cathodes at a low-temperature hinders their practical applications.
Titulo: Enhanced reaction kinetics of BCFZY-GDC-PrOx composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, BaCo0.4Fe0.4Zr0.1Y0.1O3-sigma-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 (BCFZY-GDC) composite cathode with infiltration of PrOx nanoparticles is systematically investigated.
Titulo: Enhanced reaction kinetics of BCFZY-GDC-PrOx composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is found that not only the composite cathodes demonstrate excellent phase compatibility, but also their reaction kinetics toward oxygen reduction reactions is substantially improved.
Titulo: Enhanced reaction kinetics of BCFZY-GDC-PrOx composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Simultaneously, when the amount of the PrOx nanoparticles is about 18 mg/cm(2), the R-p value of the resultant cathode reaches the minimum, and the value is about 0.082 Omega center dot cm(2) at the operating temperature of 600 degrees C, which is only 25.3% of that of the cathode without PrOx.
Titulo: Enhanced reaction kinetics of BCFZY-GDC-PrOx composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, at operating temperatures of 700 degrees C, 650 degrees C, and 600. degrees C, the single-cell's power densities with the configuration of Ni-YSZ/YSZ/GDC/Pr18 (PrOx in BCFZY-GDC cathode is 18 mg/cm(2)) can reach about 1.55, 1.02, 0.56 W cm(-2) under H-2 atmosphere, and 1.22, 0.78, 0.39 W cm 2 under 20%CH3OH-80%N-2 atmosphere, respectively, which is among the top high values based on the commercially available Ni-YSZ anode-supported single cells.
Titulo: Enhanced reaction kinetics of BCFZY-GDC-PrOx composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The mechanism investigation further verifies that the enhanced reaction kinetics can be attributed to the improved surface exchange and ion transfer at the cathode's oxygen reduction reactions.
Titulo: Enhanced reaction kinetics of BCFZY-GDC-PrOx composite cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
